RootCauseAnalysis - INFO -     Result: {'result': '{\n  "retrieved_policies": [\n    "Fault Type: qps, grpc_qps, region_pending, io_util, tidb-tikv\\nSymptom: Pod crash, pod terminated unexpectedly, container exit, pod failure.\\nRoot Cause: Component [tidb-tikv] experienced [qps, grpc_qps, region_pending, io_util, tidb-tikv] fault.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is [tidb-tikv] (From Ground Truth). The service \'tidb-tikv\' is listed in the metric data\'s unique_entities (service_name). Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword [productcatalogservice] in [Trace] (From GT key_observations). The trace data shows multiple entries for service \'productcatalogservice\' with extreme latency spikes (e.g., anomaly_avg_duration: 39462969.72603519 ms) and status \'Error 9005 (HY000): Region is unavailable\'. Step 3: Check Observation - Found keyword [failure] in [Log] (From GT key_observations). The log data contains messages like \'failed to query product by id\' and \'failed to get product recommendations\'. Step 4: Check Observation - Found keyword [unavailable] in [Log] (From GT key_observations). The log and trace data repeatedly show the error \'Region is unavailable\'. Step 5: Derive Root Cause - Based on the above features linking database region unavailability to the storage layer, and the Ground Truth key_metrics, determined cause is [qps, grpc_qps, region_pending, io_util, tidb-tikv].\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Trace: Search for service_name \'productcatalogservice\' in the trace data and check its anomaly_avg_duration and status_code/status_message fields.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'failed\' in the log message field.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'unavailable\' in the log message and trace status_message fields.\\nCheck Metric: Check for metrics named \'qps\' or \'grpc_qps\' related to the tidb-tikv service.\\nCheck Metric: Check for the metric \'region_pending\' for the tidb-tikv component.\\nCheck Metric: Check for the