se: Component [productcatalogservice] experienced [pod_processes] and [timeout] fault.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is [productcatalogservice] (From Ground Truth). Verified in Full Context trace data where `service_name` is \'productcatalogservice\' and shows severe latency anomalies. Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword [context canceled] in [Log] (From GT key_observations). Verified in Full Context log data: frontend logs contain \'rpc error: code = Canceled desc = context canceled\' when calling productcatalogservice. Step 3: Check Observation - Found keyword [timeout] in [Log] (From GT key_observations). Verified implicitly in Full Context: \'context canceled\' errors are a direct consequence of request timeouts from dependent services. Step 4: Check Observation - Found keyword [pod_cpu_usage] in [Metric] (From GT key_observations). Verified in Full Context metric data: pod_cpu_usage for productcatalogservice-1 increased from 0.0 to 0.4. Step 5: Derive Root Cause - Based on the above features (context canceled errors indicating timeouts and abnormal pod_cpu_usage), and aligning with the Ground Truth key_metrics, determined cause is [pod_processes] and [timeout].\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'context canceled\' in Log data, filtering for service_name \'frontend\' and error messages mentioning \'productcatalogservice\'.\\nCheck Log: Infer timeout by searching for \'context canceled\' errors in logs of services that call productcatalogservice (e.g., frontend, checkoutservice).\\nCheck Metric: Check the \'anomaly_metrics\' list for entries where metric_name is \'pod_cpu_usage\' and pod_name starts with \'productcatalogservice-\'.\\nCheck Trace: Analyze trace data (\'filtered_traces\') for operations involving \'productcatalogservice\' and compare \'normal_avg_duration\' with \'anomaly_avg_duration\'."\n  ]\n}'}
